# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# mfab.env — configuration for the mfab CLI tool
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# FOR HUMANS:
#   Edit this file to change which models mfab uses.
#   The active values are the uncommented lines.
#   Everything else is reference / alternatives.
#
# FOR AGENTS:
#   This file is the single source of truth for mfab model selection.
#   Before changing any model here, run:
#     fabric-ai -L 2>/dev/null | grep -v "LM Studio"
#   to see what is currently available and connected.
#   NEVER change MFAB_VENDOR/MFAB_ROUTER_VENDOR unless also changing the model
#   to one from a different provider.
#   The logic for picking models is documented in the PROVIDER INVENTORY section.
#
# FILE LOCATIONS (priority order — first found wins):
#   1. $MFAB_ENV          (if set — for fully custom paths)
#   2. ~/.config/mfab/.env  (installed by `mfab --setup`, this is the live copy)
#   3. ./mfab.env           (repo template — source of truth for defaults)
#   4. ./.env               (project-local override, lowest priority)
#
# HOW TO CHECK WHAT'S CONNECTED:
#   fabric-ai -L              → full model list (what's actually working)
#   fabric-ai -L | grep ":free"  → only free OpenRouter models
#   fabric-ai --setup         → interactive reconfigure any provider
#
# NOTE: ~/.config/fabric/.env holds provider API keys and base URLs.
#   Run `fabric-ai --setup` to add/reconfigure providers.
#   Current connected providers: OpenRouter, Groq, Ollama, LM Studio (offline)
#   Missing but available: GitHub Models (free via Copilot PAT — see below)
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PROVIDER INVENTORY & "GAS TANK" LOGIC
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# We have multiple free providers. The strategy is:
#   USE the one with the most remaining capacity first.
#   FALL BACK when rate-limited, not before.
#   AVOID Groq for MFAB_MODEL — very small context (8K-32K), bad for man pages.
#   Groq is fine for MFAB_ROUTER (single question, ~50 tokens).
#
# ┌─────────────────────────┬──────────────┬───────────┬──────────────────────┐
# │ Provider                │ Context      │ Free?     │ Notes                │
# ├─────────────────────────┼──────────────┼───────────┼──────────────────────┤
# │ OpenRouter (free tier)  │ up to 1M     │ YES       │ Best free pool.      │
# │                         │              │           │ Many big models.     │
# │                         │              │           │ Chinese models very  │
# │                         │              │           │ permissive (arcee,   │
# │                         │              │           │ deepseek, qwen, z.ai)│
# ├─────────────────────────┼──────────────┼───────────┼──────────────────────┤
# │ GitHub Models           │ up to 128K   │ YES*      │ *Via Copilot PAT.    │
# │ (NOT YET CONFIGURED)    │              │           │ 50-150 req/day free. │
# │                         │              │           │ gpt-4o, Llama, Phi,  │
# │                         │              │           │ DeepSeek, Mistral.   │
# │                         │              │           │ Setup: fabric --setup│
# │                         │              │           │ Vendor: "GitHub"     │
# ├─────────────────────────┼──────────────┼───────────┼──────────────────────┤
# │ Groq                    │ 8K-32K       │ YES       │ Fast but tiny ctx.   │
# │                         │              │           │ Router only.         │
# │                         │              │           │ Rate limits hit fast.│
# ├─────────────────────────┼──────────────┼───────────┼──────────────────────┤
# │ Ollama (local)          │ unlimited    │ YES       │ Offline/private.     │
# │                         │              │           │ Slow on CPU.         │
# │                         │              │           │ deepseek-r1:8b,      │
# │                         │              │           │ phi4-mini, gemma3    │
# ├─────────────────────────┼──────────────┼───────────┼──────────────────────┤
# │ GitHub Copilot          │ up to 200K   │ PAID sub  │ We have subscription.│
# │ (NOT IN FABRIC YET)     │              │           │ Fabric v1.4.331 adds │
# │                         │              │           │ GitHub Models support│
# │                         │              │           │ (same PAT works).    │
# │                         │              │           │ Currently our        │
# │                         │              │           │ "last resort" — good │
# │                         │              │           │ quality, costs quota.│
# ├─────────────────────────┼──────────────┼───────────┼──────────────────────┤
# │ z.ai                    │ 128K         │ PAID      │ Solid, reliable.     │
# │                         │              │           │ glm-4.5-air:free     │
# │                         │              │           │ is genuinely free.   │
# └─────────────────────────┴──────────────┴───────────┴──────────────────────┘
#
# RECOMMENDED STRATEGY (gas-tank priority):
#   1. OpenRouter free models  — burn these first, they're abundant
#   2. z-ai/glm-4.5-air:free   — solid fallback, different pool
#   3. GitHub Models (free)    — once configured, use for overflow
#   4. Groq                    — router only (fast, tiny context)
#   5. Ollama (local)          — offline / privacy / no rate limit
#   6. GitHub Copilot          — last resort, paid quota
#
# TO ADD GITHUB MODELS (highly recommended — free with your Copilot account):
#   1. Go to github.com → Settings → Developer settings → Fine-grained tokens
#   2. Create token with "AI Models: Read-only" permission
#   3. Run: fabric-ai --setup → select GitHub → paste token
#   4. Then you can use: -V "GitHub" -m "gpt-4o" etc.
#
# TO UPDATE FABRIC:
#   brew upgrade fabric-ai
#   (currently v1.4.415 — check: fabric-ai --version)
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ── ROUTER — fast model, routes questions to the right tool ───────────────────
# Requirements: must respond in <2s, only needs ~50 token context, outputs JSON.
# Groq is fine here (small context is OK for routing).
#
# Active pick: arcee-ai/trinity-mini:free  (tiny, fast, free OpenRouter)
#
# Alternatives:
#   MFAB_ROUTER="meta-llama/llama-3.2-3b-instruct:free"   # OpenRouter free, 128K
#   MFAB_ROUTER="qwen/qwen3-4b:free"                      # OpenRouter free, 32K
#   MFAB_ROUTER="stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free"             # OpenRouter free, very fast
#   MFAB_ROUTER="z-ai/glm-4.5-air:free"                   # OpenRouter free, z.ai pool
#   MFAB_ROUTER="llama-3.1-8b-instant"                    # Groq, fastest, -V "Groq"
#   MFAB_ROUTER="llama-3.2-3b-instruct"                   # Groq, tiny + fast, -V "Groq"
MFAB_ROUTER="arcee-ai/trinity-mini:free"
MFAB_ROUTER_VENDOR="OpenRouter"

# If switching to Groq for router speed, uncomment these and comment out above:
#   MFAB_ROUTER="llama-3.1-8b-instant"
#   MFAB_ROUTER_VENDOR="Groq"


# ── MAIN MODEL — what the user talks to, needs large context ──────────────────
# Requirements: handles 30K-80K token man page contexts, good instruction follow.
# DO NOT use Groq here — 8K-32K context is too small for man pages.
#
# Active pick: arcee-ai/trinity-large-preview:free
#   — current OpenRouter default (*), 128K context, generous rate limits,
#     large model, Chinese AI (Arcee), very permissive usage policy.
#
# Free alternatives (roughly ranked by quality):
#   MFAB_MODEL="nousresearch/hermes-3-llama-3.1-405b:free"  # 405B, huge, free
#   MFAB_MODEL="openai/gpt-oss-120b:free"                    # 120B OSS via OpenRouter
#   MFAB_MODEL="deepseek/deepseek-r1-0528:free"              # reasoning, great for complex
#   MFAB_MODEL="meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free"      # reliable 70B
#   MFAB_MODEL="qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-instruct:free"       # Qwen3 80B MoE, free
#   MFAB_MODEL="mistralai/mistral-small-3.1-24b-instruct:free" # solid 24B
#   MFAB_MODEL="z-ai/glm-4.5-air:free"                       # z.ai free tier
#
# Paid (use when free pool is exhausted / need reliability):
#   MFAB_MODEL="z-ai/glm-4.7"                               # z.ai flagship, strong
#   MFAB_MODEL="z-ai/glm-4.5"                               # z.ai paid, 128K
#   MFAB_MODEL="deepseek/deepseek-chat-v3-0324"             # excellent CLI understanding
#   MFAB_MODEL="qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b"                       # massive MoE, top quality
#   MFAB_MODEL="moonshotai/kimi-k2"                         # 1T MoE, 1M context
#   MFAB_MODEL="deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus"            # newest DeepSeek V3
#
# GitHub Models (once configured — free with Copilot):
#   MFAB_MODEL="gpt-4o"                                     # -V "GitHub", free tier
#   MFAB_MODEL="meta-llama/Llama-3.3-70B-Instruct"          # -V "GitHub", free
#   MFAB_MODEL="deepseek/DeepSeek-V3-0324"                  # -V "GitHub", free
MFAB_MODEL="arcee-ai/trinity-large-preview:free"
MFAB_VENDOR="OpenRouter"


# ── FALLBACK — used automatically if MFAB_MODEL fails ────────────────────────
# Should be a DIFFERENT provider/model family to avoid the same failure.
# mfab retries once with this model on any non-zero exit from fabric.
#
# Active: z-ai/glm-4.5-air:free  (z.ai pool, different from arcee/OpenRouter main)
#
# Other good fallbacks:
#   MFAB_MODEL_FALLBACK="qwen/qwen3-next-80b-a3b-instruct:free"  # different Qwen pool
#   MFAB_MODEL_FALLBACK="meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free" # Meta via OpenRouter
#   MFAB_MODEL_FALLBACK="deepseek/deepseek-r1-0528:free"         # if main isn't deepseek
#   MFAB_MODEL_FALLBACK="phi4-mini:latest"                        # -V "Ollama", offline
#   MFAB_MODEL_FALLBACK="none"                                    # fail loudly, no retry
MFAB_MODEL_FALLBACK="z-ai/glm-4.5-air:free"
MFAB_FALLBACK_VENDOR="OpenRouter"


# ── SESSION TITLER — generates smart note filenames ───────────────────────────
# Called once at exit on ~2KB of transcript. Fast + cheap is ideal.
# Set to "none" to skip smart titling and use MFAB_TITLE_FALLBACK pattern.
#
# Active: stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free  (fast Chinese flash model, free)
#
# Alternatives:
#   MFAB_TITLER="z-ai/glm-4.5-air:free"                    # different free pool
#   MFAB_TITLER="qwen/qwen3-4b:free"                        # tiny Qwen, very fast
#   MFAB_TITLER="meta-llama/llama-3.2-3b-instruct:free"     # tiny Llama, fast
#   MFAB_TITLER="none"                                       # disable, use fallback
MFAB_TITLER="stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free"
MFAB_TITLER_VENDOR="OpenRouter"

# Filename pattern when titler is "none" or fails.
# Tokens: {date}=YYYY-MM-DD, {time}=HHMM, {tool}=tool name
# Examples: "{date}-{tool}" → 2026-02-20-ssh.md
#           "{date}-{time}-{tool}" → 2026-02-20-1423-ssh.md
MFAB_TITLE_FALLBACK="{date}-{tool}"


# ── OBSIDIAN ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# MFAB_OBSV — vault root. Falls back to $OBSVAULT env var if unset.
# Uncomment to hardcode (useful if OBSVAULT isn't in your shell env):
# MFAB_OBSV="/Users/fabiofalopes/Documents/obsidian_vault"

# Subfolder inside vault where mfab session notes are saved.
MFAB_OBSV_DIR="mfab"


# ── BEHAVIOUR ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Stream responses to terminal as they arrive (1=yes, 0=collect then print).
MFAB_STREAM="1"

# Approximate token count (chars/4) at which to warn about large context.
# Warning goes to stderr only — never blocks. Lower for smaller-window models.
# Context window reference:
#   arcee-ai/trinity-large-preview:free   128K tokens
#   meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct     128K tokens
#   nousresearch/hermes-3-llama-3.1-405b  128K tokens
#   deepseek/deepseek-r1-0528             128K tokens
#   moonshotai/kimi-k2                    1M   tokens  (no practical limit)
#   z-ai/glm-4.5 / glm-4.7               128K tokens
#   Groq models                           8K-32K       (DO NOT use for MFAB_MODEL)
MFAB_TOKEN_WARN="80000"

# Prefix for fabric session names → sessions named mfab-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS
MFAB_SESSION_PREFIX="mfab"

# Number of Q&A turns before compacting session (archiving + starting fresh).
# Set to "0" to disable compaction entirely.
MFAB_COMPACT_THRESHOLD="20"


# ── ADVANCED / PATH OVERRIDES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uncomment to override default paths.

# Where curated tool context .md files live (one file per tool: ssh.md, git.md, etc.)
# MFAB_CONTEXTS_DIR="${HOME}/.config/mfab/man-contexts"

# Where archived session segments are stored on tool switch or compaction.
# MFAB_ARCHIVE_DIR="${HOME}/.config/mfab/archive"

# The active context file that fabric reads via -C mfab-active.
# Rewritten by mfab on every context load. No reason to change normally.
# MFAB_FABRIC_CTX="${HOME}/.config/fabric/contexts/mfab-active.md"
